cs.MM, cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.SD 

The paper proposes a new model that leverages visual, textual, and acoustic modalities for speaker naming in movies. This suggests that the paper could belong to multiple sub-categories such as Multimedia (cs.MM), Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV), Information Retrieval (cs.IR), and Sound (cs.SD). Among these, cs.MM and cs.CL are the most likely sub-categories as the paper deals with both audio and visual data and involves natural language processing.
